Visualize¶

Visualization.Visualize(i, n, iter, bauraum, gearbox, Anchor, EC1, EC1_width, EC1_center, EC1_SurfCenter, EC2, EC2_center, EC2_SurfCenter, EC3, EC3_center, EC3_SurfCenter, EC4, EC4_center, EC4_SurfCenter, EM_start, EM_vector, Fitness, r, y, theta, Rotations, EC2_placement)¶

Function that prints a MATLAB figure showing the best solution found by the optimization process for a defined generation of the genetic algorithm.

Parameters

  • i (int) – Counter that indicates which element of the population will be shown.

  • n (int) – User defined value that tells how many solutions per generation will be shown.

  • iter (int) – Indicates the number of generation from which the solution will be shown.

  • bauraum (struct) – struct that represents the Bauraum geometry.

  • gearbox (struct) – struct that represents the Gearbox geometry.

  • Anchor (array) – Coordinates of a point at the center of the gearbox shaft, which will be used for rotations.

  • EC1 (struct) – struct that represents the IGBT geometry.

  • EC1_width (array) – Width of the IGBT.

  • EC1_center (array) – Vector of coordinates of the body center of the IGBT, used for rotations of the component.

  • EC1_SurfCenter (array) – Array of vectors with coordinates of surface centers of the IGBT, used to calculate distance between components.

  • EC2 (struct) – struct that represents the Capacitor geometry.

  • EC2_center (array) – Vector of coordinates of the body center of the Capacitor, used for rotations of the component.

  • EC2_SurfCenter (array) – Array of vectors with coordinates of surface centers of the CCapacitor, used to calculate distance between components.

  • EC3 (struct) – struct that represents the EMI-filter geometry.

  • EC3_center (array) – Vector of coordinates of the body center of the EMI-filter, used for rotations of the component.

  • EC3_SurfCenter (array) – Array of vectors with coordinates of surface centers of the EMI-filter, used to calculate distance between components.

  • EC4 (struct) – struct that represents the Control board geometry.

  • EC4_center (array) – Vector of coordinates of the body center of the Control board, used for rotations of the component.

  • EC4_SurfCenter (array) – Array of vectors with coordinates of surface centers of the Control board, used to calculate distance between components.

  • EM_start (array) – Vector of the Electric motor center coordinates.

  • EM_vector (array) – Vector of Gearbox and Electric motor direction.

  • Fitness (array) – Array containing the fitness of the individuals for the current generation iter.

  • r (array) – Array containing the r variable of the individuals for the current generation iter.

  • y (array) – Array containing the y variable of the individuals for the current generation iter.

  • theta (array) – Array containing the theta variable of the individuals for the current generation iter.

  • Rotations (array) – Array containing the rotation variable of the individuals for the current generation iter.

  • EC2_placement (array) – Array containing the position of the Capacitor for the individuals for the current generation iter.

Example in Code

VisualizeMany¶

Visualization.VisualizeMany(n, iter, bauraum, gearbox, Anchor, EC1, EC1_width, EC1_center, EC1_SurfCenter, EC2, EC2_center, EC2_SurfCenter, EC3, EC3_center, EC3_SurfCenter, EC4, EC4_center, EC4_SurfCenter, EM_start, EM_vector, Fitness, r, y, theta, Rotations, EC2_placement)¶

Parent function of Visualize() that uses the same inputs except for the counter i. This counter is created in VisualizeMany so Visualize can be called multiple times and print many solutions. Can be used to print the desired amount of best solutions for a defined generation.

VisualizeMany(n, iter,bauraum, gearbox,Anchor, EC1,EC1_width, EC1_center, EC1_SurfCenter, EC2, EC2_center, EC2_SurfCenter, EC3, EC3_center, EC3_SurfCenter, EC4, EC4_center, EC4_SurfCenter, EM_start,EM_vector, Fitness,r,y,theta,Rotations,EC2_placement)
